Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Residential Lighting Market

The residential lighting market size is valued at USD 23,062.77 million by 2028 is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate of 6.20% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on residential lighting provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecasted period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth.

Residential lighting is the type of illuminating or lighting devices that are used in various residential households to provide desirable aesthetic and artificial lighting. These lighting products are powered through an outer power sources providing an artificial lighting solution.

The easy availability of cost-effective and attractive lights is expected to influence the growth of residential lighting market over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Also the increase in the levels of smart homes and integration of IoT services across the globe are also anticipated to flourish the growth of the residential lighting market. Furthermore, the presence of certain regulations and compliances regarding the usage of incandescent bulbs owing to their environmental effects resulting in high adoption of LED lighting is also likely to positively impact the growth of the market. Moreover, the high demand for decorative lighting in the residential segment and the high adoption of energy-efficient products such as LEDs & OLEDs are also expected create a huge demand for residential lighting as well as lifting the growth of the residential lighting market.

However, the rise in levels of rivalry from cheaper products manufactured in the China and lack of proper installation are expected to act as the major limitations for the growth of residential lighting in the above mentioned forecasted period, whereas the presence of lower quality of products can challenge the residential lighting market growth in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

Likewise, the high adoption of LED lights to replace the traditional incandescent lights and rapid urbanization in emerging economies are expected to create various new opportunities that will lead to the growth of the residential lighting market in the above mentioned forecasted period.

